Inclosed £150- : in my bill on ed. warner att 2u½ for the valeew of
Daniel Brusschep proforma for which please to procure the needfull, & place
to yd accct att 34.9 I have abour £200- . ready for my acctt which
could not send this post because of no opporsunitie, so shall remitt itt I nes
wishout faile. I have seen that m. slaughw hadt dach arrested Peeters
which I take vere un kindely, sudeed to must dave sad some more
considecaion then to afflet a or man to, I have a leder from beetere
which confirnes dis arrese & that m. psprect hade payd £140-
to m. slanghter in full of dis pretence, if that be don for caution, or tow
I know not, I am indebred £155.32 flemish, most part yett in standing
our debts, yett to make an end am ready to pay itt, so lett m. slougkes
or you draw that nede samm on mee att 2r0, & wishall send mee
accquitance, or note to dave e of mee said valeu, with the £120-
rimitted before, & the cloathes, where by de doth ericharge mee of tucl
arrest as he hath caused to be don in behalf of Peeters & hach nomore
to presend of mee, which any notary can casely fiame up so please to do
shre in what is necessary, that I may have also an end
Londen m. Abram Divran
a 17 Juni 1682
f
mij last to you was on the 10th suit, sence rec. boath yd of 26 & 29 past
the first bariug invoyce of the 60 p bayes which pray endeavour soges
a boand of smith, & do all you can bo gett ready the nordered goods by times
that by the next ship wee might have good assortement, whilss I coudd
wish yett one bale of dozens aboard Jmith, & one bale of hersies
Inclosed a fatt. of our white grayes, which you sended mee sor the bale 48-
wich now beeng all told, must save an other assortment made so 1s3
12 p fram 3.6, to 4:6 a yd raw raw, butt non exceeding 4:6, so you please
to order them to be made to purpose as least yeare for they wher good
& because wee should not stay to long for them to have them all att onee
so you maj onder yd freind so soone as any be getts ready of then, tosend
them forward amonghst other cloathes in what bales soever, then must
be 6 p. ander 4ƒ &6 p. above 4ƒ to yd ged. I am glad you reed
2 packetts by bong sea, I hope the rest is well gott to yd, handes, & coudd
with you found a good machett for f upon yd order for point de maline
have beew att Mechelen & bought some which are not yett finished, so shall
ende avour to send you an assortment toyd minde, m. noend is contended to
be concerned with you as well snthe one as other sort, & gives hen snclised
is oader to m. Pieter van de ccutt to diliver you the laces, that Iare y ett
n efective packetts, you may reed the letter & sealett itt, or if you like
them all, you can sake them to you please to speake so m. vande Prutt, &
athe un first if de sath suih laces yett as be recd. from m. moen, & that
he would please to shew them, & if then you like them you cansa thew yd ord
selling un that you have been hen, & beught them of hun for so as you shall iudge convenient. lett ma
know from bine to terne how things stand in the norch to gou my self accordingy., I nept shall
send you the acctt. of charges
Loon mr. Thomas Estabrooke
In answer to yd of 31th past einglad that you know the senes of perpetuanees I defire
sraecoiding toge promise shall exspect them, wish an acctt. of first cost, & all cariculae
charges, for which I'll see you prnetually sa tisficd, & in case itt doth give content
you may besure of a fare betder imploy, beeng with hinde saluts
London m. Luy Knigheley
a 17 g
In antwer to yd of 26 & 29 pass, have given you credit for the cost of the bale R.11:
which god be thancked is will arrived att druges, & exspected sere wishin bew dages
when shall advise you my opinnon of them, & remitt you the valed with formae
London mr. ichiel Peeters
a 17 d
met leetwesen verstaen uyt den ul van 26 patt. de absurde maniere waer mede m
slanghter ul heest beiegens, icq deb mijn gevoelen daer over heden aen hm ges
ende soo een on beleefde maniere van daen seer beriept, sij hebben £120- ste ontfl
& dat is £211- uls. daer bij nogh £155.3.2 ul tot slot van die reef., nu doesij
£140- sten nogh van m. ver spreet hebben willen ontf en weete scg niet, & wat van de
lakens gecomen is en schrijft el oocq niet, soo gelieft van alles een meerder
clarigheyt te geeven, om dat te connen regoleeren, hebbe bij ul moeden geweest
die in duijterste droesheijt is voor 2, en nogh meerder om dies wille sij geen schildrijen
verneemt, waer voor sij wel light veel sal te lijden hebben, waer om en doen ue see
veel nietom haer te onelasten, want 't is sonde & schande 't gene ul jaer aendoen
verwaghte ul adrijs van waer pars
Londn m Jac preet
a17d.
op 27 pass. heb de vrijigheyt genemen ul moylijcq te vallen in regarde van m Peetert
sedert van hem verstaen dat slaughten. hem heeft gearrest, & dat ul hem voor £ 140-
deeft gerelap, daer en tussen schrijft m. Maynard voor't slot van dun reeq 't welck
s £155.3.2 uls de welcke hem heb geord. aen m. slanghter te betj soo dat m
slaughter op reeq. van de £300- van mij deest ontf £366.3.2 ul, daer beneffens
de laeckens, & soude gij boven dien nogh £140- vragen, dat soude hem niet toecomen
ten waer sulckx alleen voor seenrisejt was geschiet, was daer van is verneme geerne
hebbe tot Brussel bij de moeden van 6 Peekers geweest, de welck ick in soodanige nocfheyt
bevonde, dat het mij uijterlijck seer doet, sij lament. seer over de schildrijen van deniers
alsoo sij voor de selve wel de uijterste noglijckheyt en schande uijtstaen, soo dieft hij
mij seer gebeden ul met desen andermael moylijcq te vallen, om te weeten ofter geen
middel can bedaght woorden daer te selven, om die schildrijen al, ofte ten decle te leeveren
wat daer van is vrneme geerne
Londen M. artsus anneslay
In answer to yd of 28 apl. last, I ave sence endeavoured all I could to sell of the serges
resting, which I have finished almost beeng vre few untold, att theend of this monch
shall send you the acctt, & seen if I shall take the rest pon mee & pay yo to make
end an end to itt all, in the meane while I am & fornced that oyl is good cherp. the
genona is demanded ben, butt most of all the gallipoyle, so that att a low machett
one may rentune to pay buy, & sowards . or oct is ordinary good sall for that hee
